The CIE Lab 1976’s color coordinates (L*, a*, b*) for the samples were measured by a portable spectrophotometer (Spectro-Guide Sphere Gloss, BYK Gardner, USA), using 10° observer with D65 illuminant configuration and d/8 viewing geometry. L* corresponds to lightness from black (0) to white (100). a* and b* are the red( +)/green( −) and yellow( +)/blue( −) chromatic ratios, respectively [9, 36]. The average values of color coordinates were reported here from the measurements performed at three different regions of the samples. The total color difference (∆E) was determined by Eq. (3) [37].3ΔE=ΔL∗2+Δa∗2+Δb∗20.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
