The antimicrobial test was performed by a liquid growth inhibition test against Staphylococcus aureus (S. aureus, ATCC 6548) and Escherichia coli (E. coli, ATCC 25,922), as reported in the literature [39]. The multifunctional wipes were cut in squares (1 cm × 1 cm) and were added to a test tube containing a nutrient culture medium (Mueller–Hilton agar, Oxoid) with the bacteria (final count of 105 UFC mL−1). The test tubes were kept for 24 h (without illumination) and 48 h (under lightning of a blue-emitting lamp of 150 Watts) in a microbiological oven at 36 ± 1 °C. After incubation, the antibacterial activity (AAc) was estimated using the absorbance of the liquid growth medium at 600 nm using UV–Vis spectrometer (UV-M51 BEL, Monza MB, Italy) and Eq. (5).5AAc%=100×Ao-AAo\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
